The bare minimum (for now):

1 - REQUIREMENTS
2 - INSTALL
3 - FIRST RUN
-------------------

1 - REQUIREMENTS
    + Python version 2.3 (maybe earlier?)
    + NOMAD (download from http://www.gerad.ca/NOMAD)

2 - INSTALL
    + Unzip the package
    + Go to the unzipped directory
    + Launch the command: 
      #shell:> python setup.py install

3 - TESTING
    Assuming your PYTHONPATH is set correctly, you should be able to do:
    #shell:> cd examples/fd
    #shell:> python fd_optimize.py
